description:
What is this course about:

This course is designed to teach parents and students how to successfully navigate and transition to a college/university. Unfortunately, graduating from college isÂ no longer is a guarantee for employment, however with careful decision-making, made both before the first day of classes and throughout the four years at a college/university, students can have a college experience that's not only memorable, but also highly productive and enriched with invaluable experiences. At the end of the course, you will be knowledgble on the following topics.

Topics Covered:

  1. Financial Aid
  2. Living On Campus
  3. Academic Advising
  4. Off Campus Housing
  5. Studying Abroad
  6. Internships
  7. Working with Professors
  8. Financial Responsibilities/Credit Cards
  9. Relationships
  10. GPA,GPA,GPA
  11. Networking
  12. Volunteering
  13. Rate My Professor
  14. Textbooks/Access Codes
  15. Fraternities/Sororities
  16. Freshman 15
  17. Majors/Minors
  18. Organizations/Involvement
title: The Ultimate Guide to Success in College
